				<td colspan="2"><span>i dont worry about keeping the drum on my curser, that is a great idea, but im not that skilled and i tend to just worry more about what my dots will do and let the real tanks deal out the melee.
<br />

<br />
my melee is so pathetic compaired to the rangers, sk, pallly, warriors in the groups i just jump in there from time to time to add a little bit of melee with my off hand.
<br />

<br />
i have noticed that my 1hb, and 1hs skills do go up when i keep my TDoK equiped as my off hand is using one of those skills and is getting the skill up.  haste really helps with this.
<br />

<br />
but to give you an idea.
<br />

<br />
bard melee = low DPS (i dont know exact numbers)
<br />
at 51 with 3 dots i do 36DPS just from my 3 dots.  that is rather nice DPS if you ask me, then i get to add in every once in a while a smack from my off hand too.
<br />

<br />
all that i can normaly twist in a 4th song for something, be it haste, slow, snare, heal, mana (now that it is icon *frown*), or DS, or resist if it is needed.
<br />

<br />
my system is nice enough that i can under normal situations keep a 4 song twist running very smooth baring fizzles.  a 3 song twist is a piece of cake.
<br />

<br />
that is why i just keep my drum in hand as i dont feel comfortable enough with my skill to add an extra click into my 4 song twist with keeping the mob in front of me, stupid chanters and their knock back spells... *grumble*..
<br />

<br />
enjoy.</span></td>
